K
L/K
\mathfrak{a},\mathfrak{b}
\mathcal{O}_K
\mathfrak{a}\mathcal{O}_L|\mathfrak{b}\mathcal{O}_L
\mathfrak{a}|\mathfrak{b}
\mathfrak{a}=\mathfrak{a}\mathcal{O}_L \cap \mathcal{O}_K
\mathfrak{a}\mathcal{O}_L= \prod_i \mathfrak{P}_i^{e_i}, \mathfrak{b}\mathcal{O}_L= \prod_i \mathfrak{P}_i^{f_i}
e_i \leq f_i
\mathfrak{a}\mathcal{O}_L|\mathfrak{b}\mathcal{O}_L
{\frak a}\triangleleft{\frak O}_K
{\frak a}={\frak p}_1^{v_1}\cdots{\frak p}_r^{v_r}
{\frak aO}_L=\prod_{i=1}^{r}({\frak p}_i{\frak O}_L)^{v_{\large i}}=\prod_{i=1}^r\left(\prod_{{\frak P\mid p}_i}{\frak P}^{e({\frak P\mid p})}\right)^{\large v_i}=\prod_{{\frak P\mid p}_i\mid{\frak a}}{\frak P}^{e({\frak P\mid p})v_{\large i}}.
v_{\frak P}({\frak aO}_L)=e({\frak P\mid p})v_{\frak p}({\frak a})
v_{\frak P}({\frak aO}_L)\le v_{\frak P}({\frak bO}_L)
\Leftarrow{\frak aO}_L\mid{\frak bO}_L
